node.text: After this past year, I like to remind myself that there is still so much to celebrate.  My Summer Rosé Sangria is here to help!  It’s refreshing and delicious and so easy to make. And all the fruit makes it good for you, right? A link to the recipe is in my bio. Happy 4th of July! 🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸

node.text:
On 9/11 when the towers were burning and people ran terrified from the buildings, many of them found themselves trapped at the end of Manhattan Island with nowhere to go. This amazing short film directed by Eddie Rosenstein and narrated by Tom Hanks, documents how ordinary Americans risked their lives to save people they’d never even met in the largest sea evacuation in history. 

Produced by Eyepop Productions
Director: @eddierosenstein

node.text: Ever wonder how to grill a perfect steak?  My New York Strip Steaks have a few tricks - thick steaks and perfect timing plus a spicy dry rub!  Thank you @lobelssince1840 for teaching me how!  Recipe on BarefootContessa.com. Have a happy, healthy Memorial Day weekend!  #staysafe

node.text: Thank you @missyarobbins for an insanely delicious dinner @misinewyork tonight.  Steak with fennel pollen & rosemary is always amazing!! #KeepItSimple

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Ina Garten on September 16, 2021. May be an image of cupcake.

node.text: So many people have asked if they can turn Beatty’s Chocolate Cake into cupcakes that I decided to test it.  The answer is YES!! One recipe of the cake makes 24 cupcakes (bake them for 25 minutes) and doubling the frosting recipe makes a little too much frosting .. but I’ve never found that to be a problem, have you?? Link to recipe in my profile! 🧁🧁🧁#BarefootContessaAtHome

Photo by Ina Garten on September 08, 2021. May be an image of dessert.

node.text:
You can be miserable before you eat a cookie and you can be miserable after you eat a cookie, but you absolutely can’t be miserable while you’re eating a Giant Crinkled Chocolate Chip Cookie!! Inspired by @sarah_kieffer, these cookies are chocolaty, crisp, and a little salty, and the perfect after-school treat with a glass of milk. Recipe link in profile.

📸: @quentinbaconphoto

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Ina Garten on September 02, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, sitting and outdoors.

node.text: Summer holidays call for hot dogs!! Instead of grilling them, we like ours cooked over an open fire. Jeffrey and I are traditionalists - potato rolls, spicy Gulden’s mustard, and LOTS of relish. What do you like on your hot dog??  Have a happy and safe holiday weekend and give yourself a break, we all need one this year!!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Ina Garten on August 27, 2021. May be an image of drink, food and indoor.

node.text: This weekend I’m making my all-time favorite summer lunch - Lobster Cobb Salad and Frozen Key Lime Pie! They require almost no cooking and they’re beyond delicious! But in the waning days of summer, I decided to add a little taste of la dolce vita - a delicious Bellini to make lunch even more special. These days we need to celebrate everything!! Link to the recipes in my profile. Have a wonderful weekend everyone!

node.text: ROAD TRIP!! With everyone traveling (safely, I hope!), I put together a fun playlist for your trip. It reminds me of the four-month camping trip Jeffrey and I took in the early 70s. (How about that 70s hair???) It’s called “Road Trip!” and it’s available on @applemusic , @spotify , and @pandora . Hope you love it!! Link to the playlist in my profile.
